The paper discusses the capacity of sparse representations for information storage, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The proposed application, Encrypted Image Folding, involves image processing and encryption, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of dictionaries for the transformation suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.SI).
